# Phase 1: Linux Navigation & File Management
- Commands: `pwd`, `ls`, `cd`, `mkdir`, `rmdir`, `cp`, `mv`, `rm`, `tree`
- Viewing files: `cat`, `less`, `head`, `tail`
- Hidden files: `ls -a`
- Exercise: Navigate your home directory, create folders, move files

# Phase 2: Linux File System Deep Dive
- Key directories: `/etc`, `/var`, `/usr`, `/home`, `/bin`, `/sbin`, `/tmp`
- Commands: `ls -l`, `du -sh`, `df -h`, `stat filename`
- Exercise: Explore directories, check file sizes, disk usage

# Phase 3: Linux Permissions & Ownership
- File permissions: `r`, `w`, `x`
- Owners: User, Group, Others
- Commands: `ls -l`, `chmod`, `chown`, `chgrp`
- Special permissions: SUID, SGID, Sticky Bit
- Exercise: Change ownership, explore permissions

# Phase 4: Linux Ownership, Groups & Sticky Bits
- Users & Groups management: `id`, `groups`, `usermod`
- Sticky bit: `chmod +t file`
- Exercise: Add users, assign groups, test sticky bit

# Phase 5: Advanced Linux Permissions
- SUID: `chmod u+s file`
- SGID: `chmod g+s file`
- ACLs: `getfacl file`, `setfacl -m u:user:rw file`
- Exercise: Set ACLs, test SUID/SGID

# Phase 6: Processes, Background Jobs & Signals
- Commands: `ps`, `top`, `htop`, `jobs`, `fg`, `bg`
- Signals: `kill`, `killall`, `trap`
- Exercise: Run background jobs, monitor and kill processes

# Phase 7: Networking Basics
- Commands: `ip a`, `ping`, `netstat`, `ss`, `curl`, `dig`
- Exercise: Test connectivity, inspect interfaces

# Phase 8: Package Management
- Debian/Ubuntu: `apt update`, `apt upgrade`, `apt install`
- RPM/Fedora: `yum install` / `dnf install`
- Exercise: Install/remove packages, check version

# Phase 9: Shell Scripting Fundamentals
- Variables: `VAR=value`, `$VAR`
- Conditionals: `if`, `else`, `elif`
- Loops: `for`, `while`, `until`
- Functions: `myfunc() { ... }`
- Exercise: Create simple scripts, loops, conditionals

# Phase 10: Logging, Backups & Snapshots
- View logs: `journalctl`, `tail -f /var/log/syslog`
- Backup configs: `cp /etc/netplan/*.yaml ~/backups/`
- Snapshots in VM: Use VirtualBox snapshot feature
- Exercise: Backup files, simulate a VM snapshot
